Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.22,0:11:33.48,Font 1,,0,0,0,,What the heck?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.46,0:11:40.33,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's this Underpants like?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.27,0:11:50.26,Font 1,,0,0,0,,To sum it up, he basically thinks\Nhe's the smartest guy in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.97,0:11:54.68,Font 1,,0,0,0,,So what's his relationship to Hirasawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.68,0:11:59.85,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Apparently, they met when they were\Nin the same seminar freshman year.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.85,0:12:03.75,Font 1,,0,0,0,,They yell at each other whenever\Nthey meet, so they don't seem friendly,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.75,0:12:05.65,Font 1,,0,0,0,,but they're actually pretty close.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.65,0:12:07.35,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.35,0:12:10.83,Font 1,,0,0,0,,So, why did he stop coming to college?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.83,0:12:15.30,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I don't really know, but two\Nyears ago, we suddenly got word
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.30,0:12:18.00,Font 1,,0,0,0,,that his only pair of pants had blown away,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.00,0:12:21.80,Font 1,,0,0,0,,and he was never setting foot outside again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.80,0:12:24.47,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Hirasawa says he's been a shut-in ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.47,0:12:28.88,Font 1,,0,0,0,,His pants? I don't get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.88,0:12:32.95,Font 1,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't take what oddballs\Nlike that say at face value.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.95,0:12:38.52,Font 1,,0,0,0,,He was boasting that he'd predict\Nall the workings of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.52,0:12:44.13,Font 1,,0,0,0,,so I bet he actually succeeded,\Nand then got sick of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.13,0:12:46.13,Font 1,,0,0,0,,That's the "World Computer" thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.13,0:12:50.12,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Yep. I'm gonna sleep a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.91,0:13:03.21,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Well? How's the real estate contract?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.21,0:13:05.31,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Pretty much problem-free.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.31,0:13:07.48,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I checked with the government office,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.48,0:13:10.75,Font 1,,0,0,0,,but I can't find anything fishy about Takky.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.75,0:13:13.92,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Okay. So all we need now
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.92,0:13:16.89,Font 1,,0,0,0,,are an official company name\Nand registration for our seal?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.89,0:13:19.59,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.59,0:13:24.10,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I wonder what we should call ourselves?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.10,0:13:28.74,Font 1,,0,0,0,,But I get the feeling that place\Nis too big for us right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.74,0:13:33.54,Font 1,,0,0,0,,What we need is the minimum amount\Nof space to maintain our system,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.54,0:13:36.18,Font 1,,0,0,0,,not a huge amount of physical room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.18,0:13:40.28,Font 1,,0,0,0,,But there might be a great way to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.28,0:13:45.39,Font 1,,0,0,0,,In zombie movies, shopping malls\Nare symbols of a decadent civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.39,0:13:48.72,Font 1,,0,0,0,,and the final paradise the minority holes up in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.72,0:13:53.36,Font 1,,0,0,0,,So that place may be our undeniable Eden.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.36,0:13:54.80,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.80,0:14:00.60,Font 1,,0,0,0,,But what if we NEETs are actually\Nthe ever-multiplying zombies?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.60,0:14:07.47,Font 1,,0,0,0,,We might not be the ones who\Nreally want to escape into the mall.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.89,0:14:25.56,Font 1,,0,0,0,,What is this? Does he use different\Naliases for different purposes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.39,0:14:26.82,Font 1,,0,0,0,,{\pos(390,135)}No, that's Akira\NTakizawa for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.39,0:14:26.82,Font 1,,0,0,0,,{\pos(250,237)}Okada is a killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.39,0:14:26.82,Font 1,,0,0,0,,{\pos(389,291)}No, this guy's Koji Kise.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.39,0:14:26.82,Font 1,,0,0,0,,{\fn\fs18\pos(270,355)}Criminal! Expose his address!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.49,0:14:30.40,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I'll get the dirt on you now, before it's too late!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.45,0:14:49.85,Font 1,,0,0,0,,It's over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.85,0:14:52.95,Font 1,,0,0,0,,The corner room on the second\Nfloor is where Underpants lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.95,0:14:55.65,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Hey, pretty cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.26,0:14:59.28,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Excuse us!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.50,0:15:04.87,Font 1,,0,0,0,,What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.87,0:15:08.10,Font 1,,0,0,0,,You received orders from Hirasawa, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.10,0:15:11.14,Font 1,,0,0,0,,He says, "Check out the old texts
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.14,0:15:16.14,Font 1,,0,0,0,,in order to find out Akira Takizawa's secrets."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.14,0:15:21.17,Font 1,,0,0,0,,It's not just the texts... we have\Nto find out what that phone is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.69,0:15:31.46,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Hello! Underpants, are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.49,0:15:37.90,Font 1,,0,0,0,,{\pos(258,206)}Yutaka\NItazu
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.46,0:15:32.79,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Oh, I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.79,0:15:35.63,Font 1,,0,0,0,,He's "Underpants" because his last\Nname looks like "under" and "pants."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.63,0:15:39.37,Font 1,,0,0,0,,"Yutaka Underpants"-- that's a great name!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.37,0:15:43.17,Font 1,,0,0,0,,You can't say stuff like that!\NYou have to be more flattering!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.17,0:15:46.37,Font 1,,0,0,0,,What? Then you call for him, Mittan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.37,0:15:51.15,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Quit shootin' off your mouths\Nin front of my damn apartment!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.15,0:15:54.64,Font 1,,0,0,0,,What, you here, Micchon?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.15,0:15:59.85,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Are you Underpants?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.85,0:16:02.72,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I got no interest in you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.72,0:16:04.99,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Is the bakery girl here, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.99,0:16:08.48,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Yeah, long time no see. How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.37,0:16:15.27,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but swing by a convenience store
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.27,0:16:18.57,Font 1,,0,0,0,,and buy me a photo magazine\Nand a literary magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.57,0:16:21.28,Font 1,,0,0,0,,What? Buy them on the internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.28,0:16:23.74,Font 1,,0,0,0,,No time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.74,0:16:27.11,Font 1,,0,0,0,,The whereabouts of the missin' NEETs,\Nthe truth about Careless Monday,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.11,0:16:30.42,Font 1,,0,0,0,,even testimony from a guy who\Nsurvived havin' his dick cut off...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.42,0:16:34.19,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Things've been developin' fast\Nhere since the PM said "Uncle"!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.19,0:16:37.56,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I can't be waitin' for somebody to ship stuff here!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.56,0:16:40.23,Font 1,,0,0,0,,You leave the phone there and go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.23,0:16:41.96,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I'll salvage it when I've got some free time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.96,0:16:44.47,Font 1,,0,0,0,,You just wait patiently in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.47,0:16:45.87,Font 1,,0,0,0,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.87,0:16:48.64,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Aw, just go buy it for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.64,0:16:50.76,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Micchon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.08,0:16:59.64,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Nice try, but I won't meet with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.95,0:17:09.79,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Say, Itazu. Are you interested\Nin Selecao-related incidents?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.13,0:17:14.23,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Don't get interested in\Nmy sophisticated research!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.23,0:17:15.50,Font 1,,0,0,0,,You'll corrupt my data!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.50,0:17:20.43,Font 1,,0,0,0,,First off, I don't want a guy who\Nwears vintage jeans buttin' in!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.43,0:17:23.77,Font 1,,0,0,0,,And I bet you just learned the word "Selecao"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.77,0:17:27.51,Font 1,,0,0,0,,from when that lamebrain\NOpposition jerk said it in the Diet!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.51,0:17:30.50,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Maybe. But you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.68,0:17:38.28,Font 1,,0,0,0,,...what if I told you I was a Selecao?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.76,0:17:45.93,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I wonder if he'll let us in when\Nwe bring him the magazines.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.93,0:17:48.66,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Who cares? I don't want to go in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.66,0:17:53.20,Font 1,,0,0,0,,But we need to get him to fix that phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.20,0:17:57.00,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I know! Why don't we buy\NItazu some gym clothes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.00,0:17:58.97,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Then he can go outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.97,0:18:02.64,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I think that would be seriously offensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.64,0:18:03.84,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.84,0:18:10.55,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I mean, I doubt he's really a shut-in\Njust because he lost his pants.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.12,0:18:14.05,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.62,0:18:20.19,Font 1,,0,0,0,,You're right...he's tellin' him to say "uncle."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.19,0:18:21.46,Font 1,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.46,0:18:23.86,Font 1,,0,0,0,,How did you catch on?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.86,0:18:25.80,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Because I did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.80,0:18:28.54,Font 1,,0,0,0,,And I think I can give you some\Nreal dirt on the NEET disappearance,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.54,0:18:31.81,Font 1,,0,0,0,,the Johnny Hunter thing that\Npeople keep confusing with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.81,0:18:39.68,Font 1,,0,0,0,,the accidents in Roppongi yesterday,\Nand their relationship to the Selecao.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.68,0:18:43.02,Font 1,,0,0,0,,On the net, it's actually the default
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.02,0:18:45.99,Font 1,,0,0,0,,to talk about the NEETs and\Nthe Johnny Hunter as one issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.99,0:18:48.59,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Who the hell are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.59,0:18:51.42,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you, I'm a Selecao.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.06,0:18:55.36,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Come on, open up, Itazu.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.36,0:19:01.57,Font 1,,0,0,0,,See, I think you'll understand what\NI mean if you analyze this phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.57,0:19:04.10,Font 1,,0,0,0,,What is that phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.10,0:19:07.37,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Each of the twelve Selecao has one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.37,0:19:10.10,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I guess you could call it a "magic phone."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.18,0:19:17.58,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I thought there were only eleven Selecao.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.19,0:19:27.89,Font 1,,0,0,0,,What is this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.53,0:19:34.23,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Hosozawa, Hasegawa, Kise, Shibuya, Okada...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.23,0:19:39.04,Font 1,,0,0,0,,The names are different, but they're\Nall the same person as Takizawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.97,0:19:44.54,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Saki, that guy is dangerous for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.81,0:19:46.37,Font 1,,0,0,0,,{\pos(298,88)}Haruo Kasuga
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.81,0:19:46.37,Font 1,,0,0,0,,{\pos(306,142)}Haruo Kasuga
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.81,0:19:46.37,Font 1,,0,0,0,,{\pos(317,218)}Sis
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.81,0:19:46.37,Font 1,,0,0,0,,{\pos(343,284)}Kazuomi Hirasawa
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.81,0:19:46.37,Font 1,,0,0,0,,{\pos(348,340)}Koji Miyano
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.55,0:19:50.82,Font 1,,0,0,0,,This is Hirasawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.82,0:19:53.42,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Hirasawa, is Saki there with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.42,0:19:56.26,Font 1,,0,0,0,,No, something came up and she went to Kyoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.26,0:19:58.26,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Kyoto?! Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.26,0:20:00.76,Font 1,,0,0,0,,It's for this Takizawa thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.76,0:20:02.96,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I sent her to see Underpants.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.96,0:20:05.43,Font 1,,0,0,0,,--Is she with Takizawa?\N--Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.43,0:20:08.30,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Idiot! How could you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.30,0:20:11.00,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Micchon's with them. What's the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.00,0:20:15.24,Font 1,,0,0,0,,That's not the issue! Come to the\Nmovie theater in Toyosu right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.24,0:20:20.58,Font 1,,0,0,0,,And check out the posts on the\NAkira Takizawa pic I uploaded to Eden!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.58,0:20:22.58,Font 1,,0,0,0,,He's a criminal!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.58,0:20:26.85,Font 1,,0,0,0,,And he might be involved\Nin a really serious incident!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.43,0:20:35.02,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.16,0:20:44.71,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I've lived in seclusion for two years\Nbecause of my missing pants.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.71,0:20:50.51,Font 1,,0,0,0,,But I feel for these 20,000 NEETs\Nfrom around Japan, my compatriots,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.51,0:20:53.35,Font 1,,0,0,0,,and I've done an about-face
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.35,0:20:56.12,Font 1,,0,0,0,,and decided to solve their\Ndisappearance from my apartment,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.12,0:20:59.99,Font 1,,0,0,0,,then go back out into the sunlight again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.99,0:21:03.48,Font 1,,0,0,0,,You better not be tryin' to trick me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.33,0:21:11.63,Font 1,,0,0,0,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.63,0:21:15.50,Font 1,,0,0,0,,The night is a seal
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.50,0:21:22.91,Font 1,,0,0,0,,If we mix in some bewilderment, it will end
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.04,0:21:34.85,Font 1,,0,0,0,,If we're in danger of wavering,\Nlet's just abandon our reasons
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.09,0:21:42.55,Font 1,,0,0,0,,We drown in dreams again
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.90,0:21:46.70,Font 1,,0,0,0,,The future stretches on uncertainly
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.70,0:21:58.05,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I can still forgive you,\NI can still know the meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.05,0:22:02.92,Font 1,,0,0,0,,The night exists to be listened to closely
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.92,0:22:09.06,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I can copy that reason, and change
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.06,0:22:19.87,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't mind cutting off\Nthe future to know your breath
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.87,0:22:25.07,Font 1,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't mind cutting off the future